Context: The George Brown College offers various programs in the field of Health and Wellness. These programs aim to improve daily life for people by providing services such as making leg braces and artificial limbs, testing hearing and dispensing hearing aids, designing physical programs for the elderly, and working with those diagnosed with autism spectrum disorder. The college provides an Entry Advising service for free to help match skills, background, and career goals with program options. Interested individuals can attend information sessions to learn more about the programs and tour the classrooms, labs, and facilities. The contact details provided are: 416-415-2000 (regular phone), TTY: 1-877-515-5559 (telecommunications device for the deaf), and ask.george@georgebrown.ca (email). The information on the website is subject to change without notice. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
